<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-02-07T12:29:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-02-07T12:29:00-05:00" n="366" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d366">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/1250</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_FDR1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Francis</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Petrograd</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-02-07T20:00:00+02:31">
                                        <hi rend="italic">February 7, 1918, 8 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received February 9, 4.40
                                    a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>2346. Nothing from Brest. Unconfirmed report that separate peace
                                concluded but conditions so outrageous that incredible.</p>
                            <p>Council by decree signed by “<persName corresp="#p_LNVU1">Lenin</persName> and five other Commissaries issued to-day
                                changes Russian calendar to accord with ours, taking effect Russia
                                February 1 which decree designates February 14 in Russia.</p>
                            <p>Patriarch, according to the laws Russian church, has excommunicated
                                all Bolsheviki because of confiscation of church property and
                                violence to clergy.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_FDR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Francis</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>